Khenari descent-records across nine cycles document the Ninth Meridian catastrophe's mortuary consequences as the largest single event of unrecorded death in corridor history.
The mass death in the thermal zone occurred faster than any existing mortuary institution could process. Bodies were consumed, records were destroyed, lineages were severed.
For Khenari, the catastrophe represents a debt: lives ended without legal registration, estates unresolved, mortuary obligations unfulfilled.
Nine cycles of descent-record review have not closed this debt because the missing persons cannot be identified without the destroyed records.
Khenari in Kiess's witness registry have filed a formal notation: the Ninth Meridian represents a gap in the corridor's legal death-record that constitutes an ongoing administrative emergency.
The notation has been acknowledged but not acted upon, because no institution has authority to close mortuary records for deaths that predate the current governance framework.
Khenari position: the deaths happened. The records should exist. Their absence is a harm, not merely a historical gap. The responsible party — the Solar Court — no longer exists to remedy it.
Kiess's three-power charter has no mechanism for assigning liability to defunct institutions. The Khenari notation remains on file as an acknowledged open debt.
Each Khenari descent-cycle, elders review the Ninth Meridian notation. It has not closed in nine cycles. They do not expect it to close in the tenth.
